This paper is about web content quality estimation, which involves natural language processing, machine learning, and information retrieval. Therefore, cs.IR (Information Retrieval) is the most likely sub-category. The paper also discusses various machine learning techniques, such as Bagging + C4.5 and multiple bipartite ranking learners, which are related to cs.LG (Machine Learning) and cs.AI (Artificial Intelligence). Additionally, the paper involves text classification and sentiment analysis, which are relevant to cs.CL (Computation and Language). Finally, the paper discusses web security and privacy, which are related to cs.CY (Computers and Society).
